{
  "texts": [
    "This mapping can be realized by any binary classifier.",
    "Instead of a {0, 1}-valued classifier, one can of course also employ a scoring classifier.",
    "For example, the output of a probabilistic classifier would be a number in the unit interval [0, 1] that can be interpreted as a probability of the preference λ a x λ b.",
    "At classification time, a query x 0 ∈ X is submitted to the complete ensemble of binary learners.",
    "Thus, a collection of predicted pairwise preference degrees h i, j (x), 1 ≤ i, j ≤ m, is obtained."
  ]
}